    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>When you want to apply different comment settings like comments per page, order of comments, &#8230;. for specific post or page, this plugin would help you do what you want.</p>\n<p>Some requirements</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your theme should compatible with wordpress 2.7 comments system.</li>\n<li>Octto wrote about <a href=\"http://ottodestruct.com/blog/2008/09/29/wordpress-27-comments-enhancements/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">wordpress 2.7 comments enhancement</a>.</li>\n<li>In short, your <code>comments.php</code> must use <code>wp_list_comments()</code> function.</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>per-post-comment-settings.php</code> to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>Why</h4>\n<p></p>\n\n"
    },
    "short_description": "You can change comment settings post by post on WP 2.7 or greater.",
    "description": "<p>When you want to apply different comment settings like comments per page, order of comments, &#8230;. for specific post or page, this plugin would help you do what you want.</p>\n<p>Some requirements</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your theme should compatible with wordpress 2.7 comments system.</li>\n<li>Octto wrote about <a href=\"http://ottodestruct.com/blog/2008/09/29/wordpress-27-comments-enhancements/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">wordpress 2.7 comments enhancement</a>.</li>\n<li>In short, your <code>comments.php</code> must use <code>wp_list_comments()</code> function.</li>\n</ul>\n",
